    {
      "content": [
        {
          "anchor": "discussion",
          "level": 2,
          "text": "Discussion",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "This method asynchronously creates a file handle for the other end of the socket connection and returns that object by posting a ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/foundation/nsnotification/name/1417116-nsfilehandleconnectionaccepted",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": " notification in the current thread. The notification includes a ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "userInfo",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": " dictionary with the created ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "NSFileHandle",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": " object, which is accessible using the ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "NSFileHandleNotificationFileHandleItem",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": " key.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "You must call this method from a thread that has an active run loop. ",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "anchor": "1817070",
          "level": 3,
          "text": "Special Considerations",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "The receiver must be created by an ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/foundation/filehandle/1409825-init",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": " message that takes as an argument a stream-type socket created by the appropriate system routine, ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "inlineContent": [
                {
                  "text": "and that is being listened on",
                  "type": "text"
                }
              ],
              "type": "emphasis"
            },
            {
              "text": ". In other words, you must ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "bind()",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": " the socket, and ensure that the socket has a connection backlog defined by ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "listen()",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": ".",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "The object that will write data to the returned file handle must add itself as an observer of ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/foundation/nsnotification/name/1417116-nsfilehandleconnectionaccepted",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": ".",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "Note that this method does not continue to listen for connection requests after it posts ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/foundation/nsnotification/name/1417116-nsfilehandleconnectionaccepted",
              "isActive": false,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": ". If you want to keep getting notified, you need to call ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/foundation/filehandle/1413309-acceptconnectioninbackgroundandn",
              "isActive": false,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": " again in your observer method.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        }
      ],
      "kind": "content"
    }
  ],
